# =============================================================================
# Two-Sample DI vs FAIMS Lipidomics Comparison Pipeline
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Input  : Two samples, each with their own blank (one DI file + one FAIMS
#          file per measurement session). Column layout in each Excel file:
#
#          DI   : mz | blank1_rep1..n | blank1_rep2..n | sample1_rep1..n |
#                     | blank2_rep1..n | sample2_rep1..n
#          FAIMS: mz | blank1_CV-15_rep1..n | ... | blank1_CV-40_rep1..n |
#                     | sample1_CV-15_rep1..n | ... |
#                     | blank2_CV-15_rep1..n | ... | sample2_CV-15_rep1..n ...
#
# Each sample is blank-subtracted with its OWN blank, IS-matched, then
# combined for comparison across sample × condition (DI / FAIMS).
#
# Outputs:
#   Boxplots  : per-lipid (S1-DI, S1-FAIMS, S2-DI, S2-FAIMS) and abundance
#               spread (same four groups)
#   Heatmaps  : S1 DI vs FAIMS best-CV; S1 DI vs FAIMS all-CVs (grey=below
#               threshold); S2 DI vs FAIMS best-CV; S2 DI vs FAIMS all-CVs
#   Excel     : 25-column comparison table (see header comments below)
# =============================================================================


